attributes.schedule:
# Schedule
## Welcome!
At the beginning, staff will present Operation Code. We'll quickly transition into sharing the code of conduct and the itinerary, as well as briefly introduce the staff.

## Network.
We'll take time to ask employed individuals to share any job postings they wish to share, and have a bit of aimless chatter to get comfortable.

## Open Source
What is it? What does it mean to Operation Code? How can you help?

## Hacktoberfest
What is it? What does it mean to Operation Code? How can you help?

## Demos
You can share you project and/or the project you're working on, if you'd like teammates! Keep it brief please.

## Breakouts
For people that feel comfortable immediately, we'll organize separate rooms/chats for teams to begin opening pull requests around GitHub! For newer developers, the Lead Engineer at Operation Code - Kyle Holmberg - will walk people through [a quick challenge](https://operationcode.org/challenge) to easily open your first pull request for Hacktoberfest!

## QnA
After the challenge is completed, Kyle will make himself available to answer any questions as long as it pertains to Hacktoberfest, Open Source, GitHub, and/or Operation Code.

At OSC, the contributors can choose their level of difficulty and also their field of expertise to start contributing accordingly, the amazing feature which saves your time and effort!
